1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Hey. Hey.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Who are you faxing so early in the morning?

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Oh, um, kind of hard to explain.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,000
I don't have a ton of contact with this Grand Branch,

5
00:00:13,000 --> 00:00:17,000
but before I left, I took a box of Dwight's stationery.

6
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:21,000
So from time to time, I send Dwight faxes.

7
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:25,000
From himself. From the future.

8
00:00:25,000 --> 00:00:29,000
Dwight, at 8 a.m. today, someone poisons the coffee.

9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Do not drink the coffee. More instructions will follow.

10
00:00:33,000 --> 00:00:37,000
Cordially, future Dwight.

11
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
No!

12
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:47,000
You'll thank me later.

13
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,000
There she is.

14
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Jan Levinson.

15
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:04,000
First thing in the morning.

16
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:07,000
Love to start the day with you.

17
00:01:07,000 --> 00:01:10,000
I'm so excited.

18
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:13,000
I'm so excited.

19
00:01:13,000 --> 00:01:16,000
I'm so excited.

20
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
I'm so excited.

21
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:22,000
I'm so excited.

22
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:25,000
Jan Levinson. First thing in the morning.

23
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Love to start my day with a hotty bowl of Jan.

24
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:31,000
Michael.

25
00:01:31,000 --> 00:01:34,000
Just call me Levinson in the morning, baby.

26
00:01:34,000 --> 00:01:37,000
Michael. Yes.

27
00:01:37,000 --> 00:01:42,000
I'm here to tell you that we are closing this Grand Branch.

28
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:45,000
I don't understand.

29
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,000
The board voted last night to close your branch.

30
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,000
On whose authority?

31
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:54,000
The board's.

32
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:57,000
What?

33
00:01:57,000 --> 00:02:00,000
I'm very sorry. I don't relish telling you this.

34
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
You've been a big part of this company.

35
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:06,000
And the board asked me to thank you for your years of service.

36
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:09,000
You're welcome.

37
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:12,000
A small number of people will be transferred to the Stanford branch,

38
00:02:12,000 --> 00:02:15,000
and the rest will be getting severance packages.

39
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:19,000
Am I a small number person, or a severance package person?

40
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
Or a severance package person?

41
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:25,000
Well, we haven't made final decisions about personnel yet.

42
00:02:25,000 --> 00:02:28,000
But you're a severance package person.

43
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:31,000
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

44
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:34,000
Oh, my God.

45
00:02:34,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Oh, my God.

46
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,000
No.

47
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,000
What are they talking about?

48
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:46,000
I don't know.

49
00:02:46,000 --> 00:02:49,000
Is it serious?

50
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:52,000
I don't know, Kev.

51
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:55,000
If you find out anything,

52
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:58,000
call me.

53
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:01,000
You got it, buddy.

54
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:13,000
Are you all right, Michael?

55
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:16,000
I'm not sure.

56
00:03:16,000 --> 00:03:19,000
All right.

57
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:22,000
You know what? I don't get it.

58
00:03:22,000 --> 00:03:25,000
I don't get it.

59
00:03:25,000 --> 00:03:28,000
Because our numbers aren't that bad.

60
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,000
Things are looking up.

61
00:03:31,000 --> 00:03:34,000
It's not all about numbers, Michael. It's about talent.

62
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:37,000
Oh, you got it. Josh?

63
00:03:37,000 --> 00:03:40,000
Our CFO believes that Josh is going to play an important role in our company's future.

64
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,000
What role is that? King of the stupid universe?

65
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Don't do this, Josh.

66
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:49,000
I think we're finished, and I need to go.

67
00:03:49,000 --> 00:03:52,000
I would appreciate it if you would please use discretion until we get our ducks in a row.

68
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:55,000
I know you're mad.

69
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
But don't do this to me. I know I hurt you.

70
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:01,000
But please do not do this to me.

71
00:04:01,000 --> 00:04:04,000
Don't hurt me like I hurt you.

72
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:07,000
Jan.

73
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:11,000
It is an outrage.

74
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,000
That's all.

75
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:17,000
They are making a huge, huge mistake.

76
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:20,000
Let's see Josh replace these people.

77
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:23,000
Let's see Josh find another Stanley.

78
00:04:23,000 --> 00:04:26,000
You think Stanlies grow on trees?

79
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:29,000
Well, they don't.

80
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:32,000
There is no Stanley tree.

81
00:04:32,000 --> 00:04:35,000
Do you think the world is crawling with philuses?

82
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,000
Show me that farm.

83
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:41,000
With philuses and kevins sprouting up all over the place right for the plucking.

84
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:48,000
Show me that farm.

85
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Pictures, memories.

86
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:57,000
Look at that. They grow up so fast.

87
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:02,000
Hey, stranger.

88
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:05,000
That sounds weird, please.

89
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:08,000
Sorry, I just feel like we haven't talked in a while.

90
00:05:08,000 --> 00:05:11,000
Well, we have nothing to talk about Dwight.

91
00:05:11,000 --> 00:05:14,000
Just do your work while you still can.

92
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:26,000
When you become close with someone, you develop a kind of sixth sense.

93
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:29,000
You can read their moods like a book.

94
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:32,000
Right now, the title of Michael's book is

95
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:35,000
Something Weird is Going On.

96
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:38,000
Colon.

97
00:05:38,000 --> 00:05:41,000
What did Jan say?

98
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:44,000
The Michael Scott Story.

99
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,000
By Michael Scott with Dwight Schrute.

100
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:50,000
Hey, did you hear about your friends in Pennsylvania?

101
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:53,000
Rumor has it that the Scranton branch is...

102
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:56,000
Really?

103
00:05:56,000 --> 00:05:59,000
That's bad.

104
00:05:59,000 --> 00:06:02,000
Sorry, Scranton branch is closing.
